entry.title: Turkey's Erdogan Leads in Presidential Runoff Election
entry.content: Millions of people voted in a presidential runoff election that could cement President Recep Tayyip Erdogan’s grip on power and his country’s influence in the war in Ukraine, the Middle East and NATO.

entry.title: Russia Launches Largest Drone Attack on Kyiv Since Start of War
entry.content: Depleting Ukraine’s air-defense stocks could be an attempt to increase the effectiveness of Russia’s future cruise-missile attacks, defense experts said.
